===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act or process of [[merge|merging]] two or more parts into a single unit.
#: ''Club '''mergers''' reduced the number of teams by half
# {{label|en|economics}} The legal union of two or more [[corporation]]s into a single entity, typically [[asset]]s and [[liability|liabilities]] being assumed by the buying party.
# {{label|en|legal}} An [[absorption]] of one or more [[estate]](s) or [[contract]](s) into one other, all being held by the same owner; of several counts of accusation into one judgement, etc.
# {{label|en|linguistics}} A type of [[sound change]] where two or more sounds [[merge]] into one.
#: ''the [[cot-caught merger]]''

